F & W CORPORATION, Appellant, v. Charles M. LOKEY, Trustee in Bankruptcy for Capitol Tobacco Company, Appellee. No. 21509. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. Nov. 30, 1964. John W. Wilcox, Jr., George W. Hood, Wilson, Branch, Barwick & Vandiver, Atlanta, Ga., for appellant. William H. Izlar, Jr., and Charles H. Kirbo, Atlanta, Ga., King & Spalding, Atlanta, Ga., of counsel, for appellee.

Before JONES and WISDOM, Circuit Judges, and HUNTER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

A careful review of the record has convinced the Court that no reversible error has been committed. The judgment of the district court is

Affirmed.
